d9bc6c2f-ebe1-4300-a836-dcb36e6454ab	Thunder Pagoda	<p>The Thunder Pagoda stands as one of the Four Monarchies of the Netherworld , a powerful faction ruled by the imposing <a href="/characters/2bb9d3d6-3255-4d81-b7c4-64b17b95bbc5" class="Editor_mention__L81up" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-mention-id="2bb9d3d6-3255-4d81-b7c4-64b17b95bbc5" data-mention-class-name="Character">@Huan Ken</a>, King of the <a href="/sites/e071e8d4-49e2-4505-9f69-8673be2826f3" class="Editor_mention__L81up" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-mention-id="e071e8d4-49e2-4505-9f69-8673be2826f3" data-mention-class-name="Site">@The Thunder Pagoda</a>. This massive structure made of shaped clouds serves as both the seat of power and the namesake of Huan Ken's domain.</p><p>At the helm of this formidable faction sits Huan Ken himself - a fearsome Uber-Boss with masterful command of both sorcery and martial arts. His authority is absolute, demonstrated by his willingness to cast disloyal subjects into random Pop-Up Junctures as punishment. Currently, Huan Ken finds himself embroiled in the Monarch War, a conflict with the Darkness Pagoda that began when <a href="/factions/830d358c-789e-4e98-b511-753a0aa8d410" class="Editor_mention__L81up" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-mention-id="830d358c-789e-4e98-b511-753a0aa8d410" data-mention-class-name="Faction">@The Dragons</a> defeated <a href="/characters/41e8e2a1-b6af-49c1-82df-4b1b7b59bfb3" class="Editor_mention__L81up" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-mention-id="41e8e2a1-b6af-49c1-82df-4b1b7b59bfb3" data-mention-class-name="Character">@Ming Yi</a> and delivered her into Huan Ken's custody.</p>	2023-09-03 18:13:35.953579	2025-07-02 20:18:11.430931	0f2b51c0-80c0-4f5f-b55f-76186903df3e	t
0efadcdd-58c6-4844-91a7-2a0527b305a2	The Ascended	<p>The Ascended are a secretive organization whose true nature lies in their origin as transformed animals who have taken human form. At the heart of their conspiracy is a rigid hierarchical structure where those of "animal stock" occupy the highest echelons of power, while fully human members (known as "The Pledged") can never rise beyond certain ranks.</p><p>Their power is derived from carefully controlled feng shui sites, particularly the Fountain of Youth, which grants immortality to their elite members. This supernatural advantage allows them to operate across centuries, manipulating events from the shadows while maintaining their human guises.</p><p>In the modern era (2032), The Ascended have escalated their technological ambitions, developing giant transforming robots like the Onryozinger AB-2, which they've used to attack rival operations such as Manly Company factories. These improbable technological terrors are powered by corrupted feng shui sites and supplemented with technology smuggled from the Cyberpunk Future through portals they control.</p><p>The Ascended maintain legitimate fronts, such as the Golden Horse casino in Macau run by Euston Chau, described as the highest-ranking member of their inner circle known as "the Lodge". They've also infiltrated corporate structures, with at least one known attempt to place an agent as a manager within Manly Company.</p><p>Their ongoing conspiracy appears focused on accumulating power through control of chi-infused sites and advanced technology, while maintaining their secret nature as transformed animals hiding among humanity. They are opposed primarily by a faction known as The Dragons, who work to disrupt their operations and feng shui sites.</p>	2023-07-02 19:31:08.313849	2025-07-20 19:07:33.967313	0f2b51c0-80c0-4f5f-b55f-76186903df3e	t
